{"key":"post-13508390","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13508390</id>\n<content>Simply build your terrarium &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;per the tek&lt;/a&gt; and it will be right.&amp;nbsp; I've used mine in less than 10% ambient humidity and it was still over 90% inside.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I suspect a crappy hygrometer, which is almost always the case.&amp;nbsp; In addition, don't hang the hygrometer on the side of the terrarium, since the air entering the holes will skew the reading.&amp;nbsp; Set the hygrometer on the perlite in the middle.&amp;nbsp; If you've built the terrarium to spec, it will work, period.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Furthermore, humidity is not the number one issue.&amp;nbsp; Fresh air is.&amp;nbsp; Blocking holes destroys both.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13509609</next>\n<prev>13507955</prev>\n<first>13501466</first>\n<last>13517092</last>\n<when>1290185453</when>\n<utime>11/19/10 06:50 PM</utime>\n</post>"}